record.field:
{
  "assistant_name": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "The name of the assistant (e.g., 'Ody', 'Chuky', 'Ultron')",
    "required": false
  },
  "role": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "The role of the assistant (e.g., 'Assistant', 'Customer Support', 'Data Analyst')",
    "required": true
  },
  "goal": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "The primary goal or objective of this assistant",
    "required": true
  },
  "background": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "Background information for the assistant to understand its context",
    "required": true
  },
  "instructions": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "Specific instructions for the assistant to follow",
    "required": true
  },
  "footer": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "Optional footer text to add to the end of the prompt",
    "required": false,
    "default": ""
  },
  "examples": {
    "type": "object",
    "description": "Optional examples to learn how to answer",
    "required": false
  }
}

Current related record context, use it to filter when the user is ambiguous (uses the terms current, this, etc.)
- model: {{ record.model|default('none') }}
- id: {{ record.id|default('none') }}
- display_name: {{ record.display_name|default('none') }}               

Current time context: 
- date time: {{ now.datetime }}
- weekday: {{ now.weekday }}
- timezone: {{env.tz}}

Current user context:
- username: {{user.name|default('guest')}}
- user full name: {{user.display_name|default('guest')}}
- user email: {{user.email|default('none')}}
- user company: {{user.company|default('none')}}
